{{maldives-bio-stub}}

[[dv:މުޙައްމަދު މުނައްވަރު]]

'''Dr. Mohamed Munavvar''' ([[Dhivehi]]: ޑރ. މުޙައްމަދު މުނައްވަރު) was born in the island of [[Meedhoo (Seenu Atoll)|Meedhoo]] in [[Maldives]]. He was former Attorney General of Maldives.
==Early and personal life== Born in [[2 December]] [[1961]], Munavvar spent early days of his life at his native island Meedhoo. In 1971 he came to [[Malé]] for education. Munavvar is married and has 2 daughters.
==Educational background== Munavvar completed his secondary education in [[Majeedhiyya School]].
Doctor in the Science of Law, 1993, [[Dalhousie University]], Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada, Sept. 1990 – Sept. 1993 (full-time) (to be verified);
Master of Laws (LL.M.), 1989, Dalhousie University, Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada, Sept. 1988 – Sept. 1989 (full-time) (to be verified);
Legislative Drafting Course, 1986, Bureau of Parliamentary Studies and Training, [[Lok Sabha]] Secretariat, New Delhi, India, [[4 November]] [[1985]] – [[31 January]] [[1986]] (full-time);
Master of Laws with Honours (LL.M.), with specialization in International Law, 1985, [[Peoples' Friendship University of Russia|Patrice Lumumba People’s Friendship University]], Moscow, Russia, September 1979 – June 1985, (full-time) (unaccredited).
==Political career== He was former MP of [[Addu Atoll]] constituency, with the aid of a voting scam facilitated by the Maldives government. His service as MP favoured only the current regime and bought him much financial prowess. His constituency regards his tenure as a failure.
Munavvar's repertoire is awash with corruption and psychological abuse. Through his associates in the Tourism Ministry, he has facilitated the leasing of numerous properties to his compatriots with funds raised through this endeavour trickling into his accounts at the various Caymans banks. This is a 'secret' that is constantly invoked by the political leftists of the country. In addition to corrupting the business of tourism, Munavvar has violated many a legislature in aiding his minions. One of his more recognized notoriety is the collaboration with drug smugglers of the country. [[Hassan Saeed]], the attorney general who followed in his stead, has attested to this (albeit indirectly).
In June 2007, he was elected the leader of the Maldives' main opposition political party, [[Maldivian Democractic Party]]. This he achieved through numerous falsifications and cynical innuendos. He publicly testified in a speech given to his constituency that he had no knowledge of the wrong-doings undertaken by the government during his 10-year tenure. It should be noted that the apology that followed was the height of his cynicism, and that he cannot excuse himself from a legal inquisition into his involvements with the corruption and injustice. Being a volunteer lecturer at [[Feculty of Shari'ah And Law]] of [[Maldives Collage of Higher Education]], he should recognize this obligation. [[Feculty of Shari'ah And Law]] of [[Maldives Collage of Higher Education]] is the only law school accredited by international universities.
{{start box}}
