Master of Laws with Honours (LL.M.), with specialization in International Law, 1985, [[Peoples' Friendship University of Russia|Patrice Lumumba People’s Friendship University]], Moscow, Russia, September 1979 – June 1985, (full-time)
==Political career==
Dr.Munavvar served as the attorney general of the Maldives for 10 years, until he was thrown away from the cabinet. He also served as the MP of Addu constituency for a number of years and this was done by rigging votes. After being thrown away from the attorney general post, Munavvar aligned himself with the opposition movement of the country, in the interest of gaining presidency of Maldives. He was jailed in 13th August 2004, allegedly for participating in the pro democracy uprising, also known as [[Black Friday (Maldives)]].
